instructText: In this next part of the experiment, please recall each story to the best of your ability.
You will be presented with the story title, names, the images, and a blank text box for each story.
Describe the story indicated with as many details as you can remember in the space provided.
When you are finished recalling one story, to move onto the next one, press the ‘return’ key.
There is a 5 minute time limit to make your response.
Please note that you will not be able to capitalize any letters except for the first letter of your answer.

recall: Thomas and sadie went to dinner together. they walked into a restaurant, but thomas asked sadie if they could be seated at the back in a booth. sadie said yes. thomas had been wanting to take some time off from his relationship with sadie because a lot of things were going on at work and he was unsure if he wanted to continue with his job. safie said that they could figure out some time apart and that to her it didn't matter, but thomas was not sure that that was the right decision. the waitress came over and they realized they had menus in front of them. the items on the menu had funny names, but they both selected familiar items. thomas picked the hamburger with a tomato and sadie asked about the reuben. later when their food came sadie got really upset and took half of her rebuen and yelled at thomas. she said she never wanted to hear from him and wanted her poloraid and beatles poster back. she stormed out of the restaurant. thomas took a bite of his hamburger but it tasted bad and fishy to him. he didn't know if to blame the restaurant or himself for the foul taste of his food.
